{
  "text": "In this section, we introduce the specific finite motivic Hopf algebra A(1) whose Picard group we will compute. Proof. This follows immediately from Voevodsky's description of the motivic Steenrod algebra [CITATION_1] . Figure 1 For our purposes, a convenient presentation of D 8 consists of two generators x and y with the relations x 2 , y 2 , and (xy) 4 . The isomorphism from A(1)/\u03c4 to F 2 [D 8 ] takes Sq 1 to 1 + x and Sq 2 to 1 + y.",
